# Design Techniques, Technologies, and Architecture

This document explains all important design decisions in this project so that a reader can understand not just what the code does, but why it is built this way.

Scope:

- techniques and patterns (for example: outbox pattern, idempotency)
- technologies (for example: Redis Streams, PostgreSQL)
- architecture and data flow
- trade-offs and known limitations
- mapping from each concept to concrete source files

