## 9) Reliability characteristics and limitations

What this design does well:

- business state is persisted before async publish
- retries can continue from DB pending outbox rows
- idempotency reduces duplicate side effects
- read state monotonicity prevents regressions

Known limitations (current stage):

- outbox publisher can emit duplicates on crash windows (consumer must be idempotent)
- retry strategy is basic (`retry_count` only, no backoff/DLQ yet)
- worker currently polls pending rows (latency/load trade-off)
- full fanout consumer, presence map, and reconnect replay are Phase 4 scope

Current outbox loop:

- [`internal/worker/outbox.go`](internal/worker/outbox.go)

