## 10) Alternatives considered (and trade-offs)

## Redis Streams vs Kafka

Redis Streams advantages here:

- simpler setup for local/single-node development
- lower operational complexity
- adequate for current phase

Kafka advantages:

- stronger durability/replay model at large scale
- richer consumer-group ecosystem
- higher scalability ceiling

Kafka trade-offs:

- heavier operations and deployment complexity
- higher cost/overhead for this project stage

Current choice rationale:

- start with Redis Streams + outbox now, harden and benchmark first, then migrate only if evidence shows bottleneck or scale requirement.

